key.name: sdpToolDescription
key.value:
Save time by running this diagnostic tool
We have identified a diagnostic package that may help us to resolve your issue more quickly.

This diagnostic package will gather information from the systems you choose, and check for certain known problems. After the diagnostic has run you will have an opportunity to view the resulting report, and can elect to upload the collected information to Microsoft. The uploaded data will be analyzed for a broader selection of known problems, and will also be made available to your assigned engineer.

If it is within your company policy to run this diagnostic package on affected systems, please follow the on-screen instructions to run the diagnostic after clicking the link. if you have any questions around the use of the diagnostic package, please discuss it further with your assigned engineer.

key.name: severityhelptip
key.value:
There are three levels of problem severity:

Severity A (Critical business impact)
The problem currently has a critical effect on my business. My business is not performing at minimal levels of performance or my business is completely down. I will provide the necessary resources to work with Microsoft on this problem.

Severity B (Moderate business impact)
The problem currently affects some areas of my business. My business has moderate loss or degradation of services. Work can reasonably continue, but only in a damaged manner.

Severity C (Minimum business impact)
The problem currently has a minimal effect on my business and I have an acceptable workaround.
